@startuml DocReady_Sequence
title DocReady Module - Order Creation Flow

actor Seller
participant Frontend
participant StripeAPI
participant Backend
participant Database
participant InngestWorkflow
participant NotificationService

Seller -> Frontend: Review tier recommendation
Seller -> Frontend: Click "Encomendar [Tier]"
Frontend -> Frontend: Redirect to /encomendar

Frontend -> Backend: tRPC orders.createCheckoutSession(tier)
Backend -> Backend: Calculate price with discounts
Backend -> Backend: Calculate VAT (23%)
Backend -> StripeAPI: Create Checkout Session

StripeAPI --> Backend: Return checkoutUrl
Backend --> Frontend: Return checkoutUrl
Frontend -> Seller: Redirect to Stripe Checkout

Seller -> StripeAPI: Complete payment
StripeAPI -> Backend: Webhook: checkout.session.completed
Backend -> Database: Create FizboOrder (status=created)
Backend -> Database: Create SellerProfile
Backend -> Backend: Create auth account (magic link)

Backend -> Frontend: Redirect to onboarding
Frontend -> Seller: "Upload your Caderneta Predial"

Seller -> Frontend: Upload PDF/image
Frontend -> Backend: POST caderneta file
Backend -> Backend: Call OCR service

Backend -> Backend: Extract: artigo_matricial, address, typology, area, VPT
Backend -> Database: Save extraction results
Backend -> Frontend: Show extracted data for confirmation

Seller -> Frontend: Confirm or correct fields
Frontend -> Backend: tRPC orders.onboardProperty(orderId, propertyData)

Backend -> Database: Create Property record
Backend -> Database: Update FizboOrder (status=active)
Backend -> InngestWorkflow: Trigger docready/order.created event

InngestWorkflow -> NotificationService: Send ORDER_CREATED notification
NotificationService --> Seller: Email + WhatsApp sent

Frontend -> Seller: "Documents processing started. View dashboard"

note right of Backend
  Account created automatically
  No password form — magic link
  Property data from OCR
end note

note right of InngestWorkflow
  Starts document procurement
  Schedules Inngest tasks
  Notifies operator
end note

@enduml
